<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
              xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
              Foreground="#E0E0E0"
              Background="#1E1F22"
              FontFamily="Segoe UI"
              FontSize="14"
              PagePadding="32,24,32,24">

    <Paragraph FontSize="28" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Export
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Foreground="#A0A0A0" FontSize="13" Margin="0,0,0,16">
        How to save a completed storyboard file for use in Urban Chaos.
    </Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,0,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Saving the Storyboard
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Once all districts and missions have been filled out, the storyboard can be saved to a <Run FontFamily="Consolas" Foreground="#E8B84B">.sty</Run> file.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Use <Bold>File → Save</Bold> to save over the current file, or <Bold>File → Save As</Bold> to choose a new file location.
    </Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/Urban%20Chaos%20Storyboard%20Editor;component/Help/Images/storyboard_export_file_menu.png"
               MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Exporting for Use in Game
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        To run the storyboard in game, save the finished file as:
    </Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Border Background="#25272B" BorderBrush="#444" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="10">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#E0E0E0" FontFamily="Consolas">urban.sty</TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Save this file into your game’s data directory so the game can load it.
    </Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/Urban%20Chaos%20Storyboard%20Editor;component/Help/Images/storyboard_export_save_as_urban_sty.png"
               MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Before Saving
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Before saving a final storyboard file, check the following:
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0" Foreground="#E0E0E0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Each district has a clear name and a sensible map position.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Each mission has a valid mission file, such as <Run FontFamily="Consolas" Foreground="#E8B84B">police1.ucm</Run>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Each mission has the correct District ID.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>The first available mission is unlocked from the beginning, usually by setting <Bold>Unlocked By</Bold> to <Run FontFamily="Consolas" Foreground="#E8B84B">1</Run>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Mission unlock chains are correct and do not reference deleted missions.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Briefing text and audio file values are filled out where required.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/Urban%20Chaos%20Storyboard%20Editor;component/Help/Images/storyboard_export_final_checks.png"
               MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Completing the Export
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        After choosing the file location and name, confirm the save dialog. The editor writes the storyboard to disk and updates the status bar.
    </Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/Urban%20Chaos%20Storyboard%20Editor;component/Help/Images/storyboard_export_complete_status.png"
               MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#3A2A2A" BorderBrush="#7A4A4A" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#E0A0A0">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">⚠ Important:</Run>
                <Run>Saving as urban.sty in the game data directory can replace the existing storyboard file. Keep backups of original game files and custom storyboard versions.</Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Basic Export Workflow
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="16,2,0,0" Foreground="#E0E0E0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Finish creating districts.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Finish creating and assigning missions.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Check mission unlock chains and briefing text.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Select <Bold>File → Save As</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Save the file as <Run FontFamily="Consolas" Foreground="#E8B84B">urban.sty</Run> in the game data directory.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Test the storyboard in game.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

</FlowDocument>
